   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">A webhook is a user-defined HTTPS request that is triggered when a subscribed event occurs
         at the Adobe Acrobat Sign. When a subscribed event occurs, Acrobat Sign creates an HTTPS
         POST with a JSON body and delivers that to the URL specified. Webhook enables real-time
         notification of workflow events such as “signed” or “created” without the need to check
         Acrobat Sign for status; your app is automatically notified when an event occurs.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">You must configure two webhooks in your Adobe Sign account:</p>
      <ul class="- topic/ul ">
         <li class="- topic/li ">Webhook to receive notifications when your document is signed or declined.</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Webhook to receive notifications when your document is sent for signature.</li>
      </ul>
